cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "External Validation of EchoNext-Mini in MIMIC-IV"
message: "If you use this software or its results, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Otabor
    given-names: Emmanuel
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-06-26
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/REPLACE_USERNAME/echonext-mimic-validation"
abstract: >-
  Independent external validation, recalibration, and fairness audit of the publicly
  released EchoNext-Mini ECG model for echocardiogram-confirmed structural heart disease,
  applied frozen to MIMIC-IV (n=47,069). Includes BigQuery label/cohort definitions,
  a WFDB-to-model inference adapter, and the full analysis pipeline.
keywords:
  - electrocardiography
  - structural heart disease
  - external validation
  - calibration
  - MIMIC-IV
  - deep learning
references:
  - type: article
    title: "EchoNext-Mini: A Dataset and Baseline AI Model for Detecting Structural Heart Disease from Electrocardiograms"
    authors:
      - family-names: Hughes
        given-names: John Weston
    doi: 10.1056/AIdbp2500516
    year: 2026
  - type: article
    title: "Detecting structural heart disease from electrocardiograms using AI"
    authors:
